Take of Sarſaparilla, ſix ounces, of Saſſafras, China and the ſhavings of Hartſhorn, each two ounces, of Liquoriſh, one ounce; 
                           〈◊〉
                         them in two gallons of Fountain-water for half an hour, afterwards let them ſtand covered in hot aſhes 12 hours; afterwards boil them to the conſumption of a third part: As ſoon as it is taken from the fire, infuſe in it half an ounce of Anniſeeds; after two hours ſtrain it, and let it ſtand till it is clear; keep the clear Liquor in Glaſs-bottles for uſe.
